#Antiulcer: against reflux
Omeprazole: proton pump inhibitor
Pantoprazole: proton pump inhibitor
H2 blocker: block histamine receptors in stomach
- Ranitidine: decrease stomach acid production

#Antiasthmatic
Epinephrine/adrenaline: anaphylaxis, cardiac arrest
Salbutamol (Ventolin)
Tiotropium (Spiriva)
Budesonide (Pulmicort)

#Analgesic: pain relievers
Non-opioid
- Paracetamol (Panadol): analgesic, antipyretic (overdose ~5g: liver failure)
- Ibuprofen (Nurofen): anti-inflammatory
- Aspirin: anti-inflammatory (overdose ~10g: brain/lungs edema)
- Naproxen (Aleve): anti-inflammatory
Opioid
- Morphine: recreational drug, found in opium, addictive
- Codeine: prodrug of morphine, found in opium
- Heroin: recreational drug, addictive
- Fentanyl: very strong, addictive

#Anesthetic: block nerve receptors, unconsciousness when general
General via inhalation
- Nitrous oxide
- Isoflurane
- Halothane
- Sevoflurane
General
- Ketamine
- Propofol: intravenous
- Thiopental: intravenous
Local: blocks sodium channels on neuron membrane
- Lidocaine
- Benzocaine
- Bupivacaine

